Nov. 05, 2023, officially GRADUATED!
I want to dedicate this achievement to all of you: To all those who have inspired me, to all those who trusted me, supported me, and believed in me, thank you...
To my managers: Dr. Ainhoa Llorente, mentors: Marwen Khazri, Meher Bnouni, Ahmed Cheikh Rouhou, and work colleagues with whom I worked, learned from, and grew with, forever grateful for all that I have learned from you.
To all my professors who were instrumental in my learning journey at Esprit School of Business, IHEC Carthage I have attended.
Today, I am thrilled to share that I have finally and officially graduated with high honors as a Business Analyst from the Esprit School of Business.
Reflecting on the past seven years of university, from having to obtain a master's degree in Supply Chain Management from IHEC Carthage to obtaining a master's degree in business Analysis. I have had the opportunity to volunteer, and be a part of various student clubs and organizations, wear many hats, and dabble in different fields ranging from a supply manager to a business analyst...
In addition to my academic pursuits, I have been fortunate to embark on internships with different companies and organizations InstaDeep, KPMG, TheSparksFoundation, Brandee...
Each experience has been a unique building block in shaping who I am today, personally and professionally. I am deeply grateful for the knowledge,
skills, and countless opportunities these organizations provided me during my student journey.
I am hopeful and excited about the future, and I can't wait to continue to learn and give back.
